===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Uncertain. At least three theories exist:

According to the version on bronzes and Yu Shengwu (дәҺзңҒеҗҫ), [[иҫӣ]] ("chisel to mark prisoners") + [[дәә]] ("man"); the character indicates a punishment and, according to Yu Shengwu, it is the original version of [[й»Ҙ]]. Compare the phonetic component of [[жҺҘ]].

According to He Linyi (дҪ•зҗіе„Җ), it is the contraction of the character [[з«¶]].

According to ''{{w|Shuowen}}'', it is an {{Han compound|йҹі|е„ҝ|t1=sound|t2=man|ls=ic|nocap=1}} (originally written as иҲҢ and дәә) - a man has spoken. This interpretation is partly related to [[з«¶]].

===Etymology===
